commText: Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Boult will open the attack
Boult to Philip Salt, no run, inswinger bowled on a length, Salt looks to defend leg-side and gets it off the splice to the right of mid-wicket

Boult to Philip Salt, no run, Parag drops the dolliest of dollies. He tries for the Australian style reverse cup and puts it down. Swinging away in the outside off channel, Salt pokes with hard hands on the front foot and the outside edge goes flying straight to backward point where Parag fails to hold on...Had all the time in the world and barely had to move, he took a couple of strides to his left and makes a meal of it...
Boult to Philip Salt, no run, full on off, Salt pins the drive to the left of cover
Boult to Philip Salt, 2 runs, skiddy length delivery on midle and leg, Salt flicks it off the splice to the right of mid-wicket. Easy two...
Boult to Philip Salt, no run, beats him all ends up on the outside edge. Good length swinging away in the corridor of uncertainty, Salt looks to push and got done by the late away movement
Boult to Philip Salt, no run, good length swinging in towards middle and leg, Salt shows full face of the bat and blocks into the off-side
Avesh Khan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Avesh Khan to Narine, 1 run, width on offer outside off, Narine makes room and slices it to the right of sweeper cover
Avesh Khan to Philip Salt, 1 run, full and swinging in towards off at I0$, Salt slogs and gets it off the thick inside half to the left of the fielder at deep square
Avesh Khan to Narine, no run, shaping away outside off with extra bounce at I0$, Narine shapes up for the pull and gets beaten by the pace and extra bounce

Avesh Khan to Narine, byes, FOUR, bumper that pitches outside leg and leaves Narine ducking for safety. He was a bit late to duck, but the ball kicks up sharply and beats the leaping keeper to his right

Avesh Khan to Narine, FOUR, one bounce and over the ropes! Slower full delivery bowled outside off at I0$, Narine slogs and gets it off the toe end over mid-on, the impact (of the bottom hand) on the shot takes care of the rest
Avesh Khan to Narine, no run, fuller and wider of off, Narine looks to smash it down the ground and gets beaten on the outside edge

Boult to Philip Salt, 2 runs, I0$ short of length on middle and leg, Salt heaves leg-side and drags it off the thick inside half over mid-wicket. Avesh Khan ran back but the ball was always gonna tease him...
Boult to Philip Salt, 1 run, I0$ full on leg stump, Salt flicks to the right of mid-wicket for a quick single
Boult to Narine, no run, I0$ swinging away from a length outside off, Narine tries to steer it towards point and gets beaten on the outside edge
Boult to Narine, 1 run, I0$ dug in short outside off, Narine slaps the pull and gets it off the toe-end to the right of the bowler

Boult to Philip Salt, FOUR, there's the first boundary Salt was searching for. A I0$ full delivery outside off, Philip Salt brings his bat down at a straight angle and thumps the drive straight past the fielder at mid-off
Boult to Philip Salt, no run, bumper at the batter, Salt swivels and fails to get any contact on the attempted pull. Takes a blow around the shoulder...
Avesh Khan to Narine, 1 run, I0$ length ball wide of off, Narine heaves and drags it off the toe end to the right of mid-on
Avesh Khan to Philip Salt, no run, looks to go hard on the leg-side and picks out the fielder at mid-wicket
Avesh Khan to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Avesh Khan to Philip Salt, out Caught&Bowled!! Parag will be chuffed to bits because his drop didn't prove too costly. He must thank Avesh a lot though for it's a stunner of a return catch. Dragged the length back and kept it wide of off, Salt wanted to smash it flat straight past the bowler but skewed it off the thick inside half of the bat. It went low flying to the left of Avesh who managed to stick his hand out to take a well-judged low catch. Top stuff. Philip Salt c and b Avesh Khan 10(13) [4s-1]
Angkrish Raghuvanshi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Avesh Khan to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, back of a length on off, Raghuvanshi drops the ball with soft hands on the leg-side and hares across for a quick single
Avesh Khan to Narine, FOUR, width on offer outside off, Narine slices the low full toss square on the off-side and the fielder at backward point had no chance whatsoever...
Avesh Khan to Narine, no run, I0$ back of a length that pitches outside leg with a hint of extra bounce, Narine swivels across to pull and misses. Takes a blow on the hip...
Boult to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, inswinger on middle and leg, Raghuvanshi shuffles down the pitch and unleashes his wrists on the flick that goes racing along the ground through mid-wicket
Boult to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, I0$ good length on off, tucked away into the leg-side for a quick single
Boult to Narine, no run, I0$ swings late into the pads, Narine slogs and misses. The ball takes the pad and drops short of slip to his left
Boult to Narine, 1 run, I0$ full outside off, Narine slices the loft off the toe-end down to long-off
Boult to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, full and wide of off, Raghuvanshi opens the bat face and slices the drive to the left of backward point

Boult to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, I0$ errs on the fuller length once again and Raghuvanshi takes full toll of it. Leans on the front foot and times the drive to absolute perfection. Off she goes through covers...

1-5 Over Summary: -- Salt dropped on 0 by Parag, a dolly off Boult's bowling -- A couple of fours in the 2nd over -- High-risk batting & Salt collects his 1st boundary -- Avesh takes a stunning return catch to remove Salt -- Three boundaries off Boult for Raghuvanshi in an over
Kuldeep Sen, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, leg byes, FOUR, I0$ short and drifting down leg, Narine went for the pull and seems to have gotten it off his hip as the ball deflects past the diving right hand of the keeper
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, 1 run, short and wide of off at I0$, Narine slices the cut and the fielder at deep backward point collects it on the bounce
Kuldeep Sen to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, I0$ short of length outside off, Raghuvanshi cuts but can't beat backward point to his right
Kuldeep Sen to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, slashes at a I0$ short and wide delivery, gets it off the thick toe-edge to the left of third man

Kuldeep Sen to Narine, SIX, there's the first six of the night and it's a huge one from Narine. Short and right in the arc just outside off, Narine sat back waiting for something short and he's smoked that into the mid-wicket orbit with terrific timing
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, FOUR, and now he goes straight. Meets the full ball from outside off and clubs it back over the bowler's head with plenty of bottom hand power. 16 off the over.
Trent Boult in the Powerplay in IPL 2024 \nFirst three matches: 5/58 (9 overs, SR: 10.8, ER: 6.44) \nNext four matches: 0/63 (10 overs, ER: 6.3)
Timeout! First 4 overs - 26/1. Last 2 overs 30/0. Did RR miss a trick by not trying spin against Narine in the powerplay? Only time will tell...
Yuzvendra Chahal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, tossed full and just outside off, Raghuvanshi gets on the front foot and pushes the drive to cover
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, Raghuvanshi toe-ends the drive to the right of long-on
Chahal to Narine, 1 run, pitches outside leg and drifts in towards middle, Narine looks to flick and seems to have gotten an inside edge onto pad that rolls into the off-side
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, sloppy from Parag once again. Flicked away to the right of long-on and despite a well-timed dive. Parag couldn't hold onto the ball...
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, floated up on the stumps, eased down to long-off
Chahal to Narine, 1 run, quicker on leg stump, flicked away to the left of deep mid-wicket
Ravichandran Ashwin, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Ashwin to Narine, 1 run, low full toss wide of off, Narine pushes the drive to long-off
Ashwin to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, floated up on middle and leg, tucked away into the leg-side
Ashwin to Narine, no run, full and wide of off, left alone to the keeper
Ashwin to Narine, FOUR, one bounce and over the ropes. Ashwin tosses it a bit fuller outside off, Narine thumps the lofted drive through extra cover and the fielder in the deep had no chance...
Ashwin to Narine, FOUR, brings up the 50-run stand. Short and wide of off, Narine slashes hard and the outside edge flies past the diving right hand if backward point

Ashwin to Narine, no run, Narine tries to go for the switch hit and gets beaten the pace of the delivery, Samson whips the bails and appeals for a stumping but umpire Michael Gough at square leg shows no interest whatsoever...
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, quicker legbreak outside off, Raghuvanshi uses the depth of the crease and cuts it really late in the gap between backward point and short third
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full on off, Raghuvanshi pushes it to the right of cover and hustles across for a quick single
Chahal to Narine, 1 run, googly bowled full and wide of off, Narine slogs and gets it off the bottom half to the right of long-on
Chahal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, full and just outside off, Raghuvanshi whips it off the thick inside half to the left of deep mid-wicket
Chahal to Narine, 2 runs, slower and shorter outside off, Narine punches off the back foot to the right of long-off and Parag manages a clean stop this time around
Chahal to Narine, SIX, slow and full, right in the slot outside off. Narine clears his front leg and tonks it straight down the ground for his second maximum. 15 off the over
Ashwin to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, flat on middle and leg, clipped away into the mid-wicket pocket
Ashwin to Narine, no run, short and wide of off, Narine looks to slash and gets a thick inside edge onto pad
Ashwin to Narine, 1 run, low full toss outside off, Narine toe-ends the drive to the right of deep extra cover
Ashwin to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, short on off stump, worked away wide of long-on

Ashwin to Narine, wide, full toss sprayed wide of off, just past the guide line as Narine swings and misses. Both Ashwin and Samson get together and decide to review that call. No dice. RR now have just one review left

Ashwin to Narine, SIX, and to rub salt into the wounds Narine has marmalized Ashwin straight down the ground to bring up his fifty. Fuller and in the slot, next thing Ravichandran saw was the ball flying over his head and into the crowd...
Ashwin to Narine, 1 run, full toss just outside off, Narine heaves and drags it off the inside half to the left of deep mid-wicket

6-10 Over Summary - 60/0: -- 16 runs off the final over of the powerplay -- Back-to-back fours for Narine vs Ashwin -- Fifty stand between Narine & Raghuvanshi -- 15 runs off Chahal's 2nd over -- 29-ball fifty for Narine
Kuldeep Sen [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, wide, bumper angling down leg, Narine lets it pass

Kuldeep Sen to Narine, no run, I0$ bumper wide of off, Narine hops and leaves it alone. Did he expect it to be a wide for height? Not too sure, but it was just around head high and won't be called a wide
Looks like Sanju Samson has got a minor injury concern and hence the brief delay as the physio tends to him....
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, FOUR, I0$ short and wide of off, Narine says thank you and spanks it along the ground through extra cover with lots of bottom hand power...
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, 1 run, I0$ bumper angled into the body, Narine swivels and drags the pull to the left of deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Sen to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Sen to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Caught by Ashwin at third man!! Much-needed breakthrough for the Royals. I0$ short and wide of off, Raghuvanshi was all hands on the attempted slash. Slices it off the thick top-edge and picks out the fielder at third man to absolute perfection. Angkrish Raghuvanshi c Ashwin b Kuldeep Sen 30(18) [4s-5]
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Sen to Shreyas Iyer, no run, skiddy length delivery just outside off, solid block from the skipper
Kuldeep Sen to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, full and wide of off, Iyer takes a step back and opens the bat face really late to slice it behind point. I0$
Ashwin to Narine, wide, full and well wide of off, Narine shoulders arms
Ashwin to Narine, no run, once again stick to the wide line and gets it inside the guide line this time, Narine doesn't bother with it
Ashwin to Narine, SIX, launched! A gentle short delivery outside off, Narine transfers his weight on the back foot and smokes it straight down the ground for an 82-metre maximum
Ashwin to Narine, FOUR, Ashwin goes fuller and wider of off, Narine says thank you and slaps it straight back over the bowler's head. No chance for Powell at long-off running across to his left
Ashwin to Narine, no run, goes full and wide of off, just around the guide line as Narine shoulders arms
Ashwin to Narine, no run, make that two in a row. Full and fast flirting with the wide line, Narine lets it be
Ashwin to Narine, FOUR, no escaping this time around. Low full toss wide of off, Narine smacks the drive off the meat to the right of extra cover, the fielder at long-off had no chance
Yuzvendra Chahal [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
Chahal to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, full on off, Iyer flicks it to the right of deep mid-wicket
Chahal to Narine, 1 run, short and just outside off, Narine pulls it off the thick inside half to the left of long-off
Chahal to Shreyas Iyer, no run, spins away sharply just outside off, Iyer hangs on the back foot and gets beaten on the outside edge
Chahal to Shreyas Iyer, no run, full outside off, Iyer drives and finds the fielder at cover
Chahal to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, floated up just outside off and right in the arc for Shreyas Iyer who sends it packing over wide long-on with a well-timed slog

Shreyas Iyer given out lbw. KKR review. Doesn't seem to be any bat involved. UltraEdge confirms no bat. Iyer has started to walk already, well before the ball tracking picture. Three reds. Done. KKR have lost a review as well
Chahal to Shreyas Iyer, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Chahal to Shreyas Iyer, out Lbw!! Chahal slips in a googly and beats Shreyas Iyer on the slogsweep. Past the bottom edge and hits him dead in front of middle and off. Umpire Michael Gough was quick to raise his finger and Iyer was too optimistic in taking that review. Ball tracker shows it was gonna hit the top of middle. Shreyas Iyer lbw b Chahal 11(7) [4s-1 6s-1]
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Ashwin to Narine, wide, tossed up well outside off, Narine lets it go. Wided by the umpire

Ashwin to Narine, 2 runs, in the air... but safe! Ashwin pushes this one wide outside off and Narine was expecting it. So he shuffles across his stumps and throws his bat at it. Ends up slicing it but it falls in no man's land
Ashwin to Narine, wide, Ashwin once again targets the tramline but bowls it beyond the tramline
Ashwin to Narine, 5 wides, Ashwin overcorrects this time and slips a full ball down leg, goes past Narine's attempted flick and Samson can't collect it either. Bonus runs these

Ashwin to Narine, 1 run, in no man's land once again! Ashwin tosses this one up nicely well outside off, Narine chases it and miscues the lofted stroke over extra cover. The fielder runs in from the deep but it lands short of him
Ashwin to Russell, 2 runs, drifting towards the pads, Russell plays it with soft hands towards fine leg and rushes back for the second run
Ashwin to Russell, no run, turning in from a length, Russell works it to backward square leg
Ashwin to Russell, no run, quicker and flatter this time, grips and turns, Russell pokes at it and gets an inside edge onto the pads
Ashwin to Russell, 1 run, slower through the air and turning in, Russell waits for it and works it round the corner to retain strike. An off day with the ball for Ashwin
Kuldeep Sen [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Sen to Russell, no run, Russell makes room to unsettle the rhythm of Kuldeep Sen but he bowls a length ball smartly away from his reach. Russell swings and misses

Kuldeep Sen to Russell, FOUR, this time he connects! Kuldeep Sen decides to bowl this one on a back of a length and offers some width, Russell cashes in and upper cuts it over backward point for a one-bounce boundary
A deep backward point in place now and third man also in place
Kuldeep Sen to Russell, wide, the plan is clear - to bowl well outside off but this one is beyond the tramline, wided
Kuldeep Sen to Russell, 1 run, 144.2kph back of a length ball wide outside off, Russell has to reach out to it and can only punch it to sweeper cover

Kuldeep Sen to Narine, FOUR, edged and four! It's Narine's night! Fullish ball outside off, room to play with and Narine throws the kitchen sink at it. It flies off the outer half past short third for a boundary
Kuldeep Sen to Narine, 1 run, back of a length ball angling in from round the wicket, rushes Narine for pace. He mistimes the pull through mid-wicket

Kuldeep Sen to Russell, FOUR, well placed! A low full-toss wide outside off, Russell was expecting this line. He gets low in his stance, opens his bat-face and carves it past backward point. Beats the man at squarish third man with ease too. 15 off the over

11-15 Over Summary -- 61/2: -- Sen breaks the 85-run stand; Raghuvanshi out for 18-ball 30 -- 15 runs off Ashwin's 3rd over -- 6 & OUT; Chahal traps Shreyas lbw -- Ashwin's bowling figures today - 4-0-49-0 -- 14 runs off the 15th over
Yuzvendra Chahal [3.0-0-31-1] is back into the attack
Chahal to Narine, 1 run, 90.2kph tossed up delivery sliding across Narine. He shuffles a bit and drags the slog sweep off the inner half towards short fine leg
Chahal to Russell, 1 run, the googly on a back of a length on middle, Russell reads it off the pitch and works it to deep mid-wicket
Chahal to Narine, SIX, going, going and gone! Narine uses his feet, gets close to the pitch of the ball, and smashes it over long-off for a maximum. Was the googly and he picked it to perfection

Chahal to Narine, FOUR, Narine moves into the nineties! There's no stopping him tonight! A googly but it's on a back of a length outside off, allows ample time for Narine to line it up. He stands tall and flat-bats it down the ground. Bisects long-off and long-on to perfection
Chahal to Narine, wide, quicker and flatter but wide outside off, wided
Chahal to Narine, SIX, this is poor bowling! Short this time outside off, Narine gets into a good position and flat-bats it straight as arrow for a maximum. Russell at the other end is loving it

Chahal to Narine, FOUR, take a bow, Narine! A brilliant century for Narine! He raises his bat, doesn't show much emotions but he must be elated! Gets a hug from his batting partner. The crowd is up on its feet and giving him a standing ovation! Has been an exhibition of clean hitting! Tossed up outside off, Narine shuffles a bit and slog sweeps it past the left side of long-on to find the fence

Time for the strategic break! Live visuals showed that Gambhir hugged Narine. KKR are well placed to cruise past 200. They will be eyeing at least 50 in the last four overs with Narne and Dre Russ out in the middle
Avesh Khan [2.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack
Avesh Khan to Russell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Avesh Khan to Russell, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! No carnage from Russell tonight! On a back of a length wide outside off, Russell has to reach out to it and mistimes his expansive shot over covers. Jurel in the deep takes an easy catch. Was the slower one and hence he couldn't generate enough power through the shot. Russell c Dhruv Jurel b Avesh Khan 13(10) [4s-2]
Rinku Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Avesh Khan to Rinku Singh, 1 run, back of a length ball angling in from round the wicket, Rinku Singh pushes at it and gets an outside edge towards third man
Avesh Khan to Narine, wide, 129.5kph short ball angling in from round the wicket, Narine ducks under it. Too high and it's been wided
Avesh Khan to Narine, no run, a full ball well outside off, Narine doesn't go after it. A rare dot ball
Avesh Khan to Narine, no run, brilliant stuff from Avesh Khan! Nails a yorker length ball just outside off, Narine looks to carve it away but can't connect

Avesh Khan to Narine, FOUR, nothing wrong with this delivery, it's again almost on a yorker length but Narine is in such a zone tonight. He opens the face of his bat and carves it past the left of backward point to find the fence
Avesh Khan to Narine, 1 run, 119,7kph slower short ball angling into Narine. He hops and pulls it to deep mid-wicket to retain strike. Only 7 off the over, brilliant over from Avesh Khan
Trent Boult [3.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack
Boult to Narine, no run, slower bouncer outside off at 120.3kph, Narine is ages early into his pull shot and only connects thin air
Boult to Narine, FOUR, pace on this time at 133.2kph and it's on a back of a length outside off, sits up nicely for Narine. He nails the pull over mid-wicket for a boundary
Boult to Narine, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Boult to Narine, out Bowled!! Knocked him over! It has been a sensational knock from Narine and Boult congratulates him on his way back! He nails the yorker this time as it tails in at good pace, Narine clears his front leg and tries to whack it across but misses. The ball crashes into the leg-stump. A standing ovation for Narine! Narine b Boult 109(56) [4s-13 6s-6]
Narine vs Ashwin in the IPL Runs: 94 Balls: 39 Dismissals: 1 SR: 241.02 4s/6s: 9/7 Today: 34 off 17, four fours and two sixes
IPL hundreds for KKR 158* - Brendon McCullum vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2008 105* - Sunil Narine vs RR, Kolkata, 2024 104 - Venkatesh Iyer vs MI, Mumbai WS, 2023
There's a bit of a delay. The yorker from Boult disturbed the leg-stump. The staff is out and they are getting things sorted
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Boult to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, Venkatesh Iyer uses his feet and flicks the full-toss to wide long-on and rushes back for the second run
Boult to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, a skiddy good length ball shaping in on off, Venkatesh Iyer punches it to mid-off for a brisk single

Boult to Rinku Singh, no run, close shave! Rinku Singh makes room and Boult bowls a inswinging yorker length ball around off. He swings and misses and the ball almost kisses the off-stump. Another tidy over, RR are pulling things back a bit at the backend
Avesh Khan to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, a very full ball on off, Venkatesh Iyer can only push it down the ground towards mid-off
Avesh Khan to Rinku Singh, SIX, brilliant shot! Rinku Singh backs away and Avesh Khan bowls a slot ball. He has space to free his arms and launches it over deep extra cover for a maximum
Avesh Khan to Rinku Singh, FOUR, Rinku Singh is on the charge! He once again makes room and this one is fuller in length on off. Rinku Singh carves it over backward point to get the desired result
Avesh Khan to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 121.8kph slower length ball this time, Rinku Singh punches it to covers and scurries across to the other end
Avesh Khan to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, 139.6kph full ball shaping across Venkatesh Iyer. An ugly heave across the line from Venkatesh Iyer after advancing and he misses

Avesh Khan to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, Avesh Khan misses his mark slightly and pays for it. Goes for the yorker but ends up bowling a low full-toss outside off, Venkatesh Iyer hits it hard over point for a rocketing boundary. 16 off the over
Kuldeep Sen [3.0-0-37-1] is back into the attack

Kuldeep Sen to Rinku Singh, 1 run, what an effort from Parag! If he had taken it, it would have been outstanding! Was a back of a length ball around off, Rinku Singh flat-bats it towards long-on. Parag near the ropes leaps and takes it overhead. The momentum is taking him beyond the ropes so he flicks it back in before going over. It is checked upstairs and he fine. Brilliant
Kuldeep Sen to Venkatesh Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Sen to Venkatesh Iyer, out Caught by Dhruv Jurel!! A full ball wide outside off, Venkatesh Iyer slices his lofted stroked over extra cover. Jurel in the deep moves to his left, runs in, and gets low to take a briliant catch. A fielder was coming in from covers but Jurel did well to focus completely on the ball. Venkatesh Iyer c Dhruv Jurel b Kuldeep Sen 8(6) [4s-1]
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Sen to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, a pinpoint yorker on off, Ramandeep Singh drags his shot to deep square leg
Kuldeep Sen to Rinku Singh, no run, a slower full ball wide outside off, Rinku Singh can only drill it to covers
Kuldeep Sen to Rinku Singh, SIX, boom goes Rinku Singh! A short ball that sits up nicely for Rinku Singh. He stands tall and pulls it with aplomb over deep mid-wicket for a maximum

Kuldeep Sen to Rinku Singh, 1 run, a full ball shaping in, Rinku Singh hits it really well but it goes onto hit the stumps at the other end. The ball deflects to the bowler's right and the batters take a single. KKR finish with 223/6

21:23 Local Time, 15:53 GMT, 21:23 IST: RR pulled things a bit at the backend but the damage was already done before that, courstesy a scintillating century from Narine! Salt was dropped for a duck but he couldn't take advantage of it as he fell shortly after that as Avesh took a brilliant return catch. Angkrish Raghuvanshi came in and looked fluent from the word go while Narine also grew in confidence by hitting some expansive shots. A cameo from Raghuvanshi kept things moving - after his fall, Shreyas Iyer also fell cheaply against the run of play. But, there was no stopping Narine as he tore into the RR bowlers. He hit the ball all around the park and made the best bowling attack of this season so far look ordinary. Avesh and Boult were the only ones who conceded less than 10 an over. A breezy cameo from Rinku SIngh helped KKR's cause as they propelled to a massive score. But, this is a great track for batting and with short boundaries, no score is safe. SRH gave the home side a run for their money when they scored 208. Should be an exciting chase! Join us shortly...

Sunil Narine: (At the start of the season if anyone had told him he'd be in the race for the Orange cap) I would have taken it as a joke because I haven't opened in such a long time or did much with the bat in the years past. (Opening this year) With GG (Gambhir) coming back, he gave me the confidence and his assurance that I'll open the batting. (Mindset) The job is just to go out there and try to give a good start, whatever the situation is, still keep going because if you try to face dot balls in the powerplay, it could hurt you in the backend. So just go there and try to give your team a good start. We have an understanding about it, it's not going to be easy (bowling here), we have to make use of the powerplay, pick up early wickets and make sure that we control in the middle and try to restrict them. ("I will be watching it from home, Badree," were Narine's words after previous match when asked if he could make it to the T20 WC. When asked about that statement today) It is what it is, we'll have to see what the future holds.
